cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.CV, cs.GT. 

This paper is about improving the AlphaZero algorithm, which is a machine learning algorithm used for playing games. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also discusses hyperparameter tuning and population-based training, which are topics related to machine learning and optimization, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) likely categories as well. The paper also uses neural networks, which falls under cs.CV (Computer Vision). Finally, the paper is about playing games, which falls under cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory).
